<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{y}=-{59}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{4}{x}+{7}{y}=-{49}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},-{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -4. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{4}}{{8}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{4}}}{{8}}{\left({8}{x}+{1}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{4}}}{{8}}{\left(-{59}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({4}\right)}{x}+-{0.5}{y}={29.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}+{7}{y}=-{49}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6.5}{y}=-{19.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{19.5}}{{6.5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{1}{\left(-{3}\right)}=-{59}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{\left(-{3}\right)}=-{59}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}=-{59}-{\left(-{3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}=-{56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{56}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7},-{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

